Kairu Aminus revealed that the latest batch of anti-counterfeiting paper has arrived in Kuala Lumpur on the 6th of this month, after which it was handed over to the printing company on the 8th for part of the printing work.
"The bureau will send someone to Kuala Lumpur next Thursday to pick up the goods, back to Sabah immediately for the final stage of printing, it is estimated that 2 more working days (December 20) can be handed over to the applicant . "
